The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.
The Court finds him not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but does find him eligible for the Substance Abuse Program after serving the first year of initial confinement. 
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay $1,200.00 fine plus costs, total of $2,527.00.  $1,000.00 cash bail applied;
2) Undergo Intoxicated Driver Assessment and Drive Safety Plan;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
Court further orders thirty-six (36) month DL revocation and period of Ignition Interlock.
The defendant has credit for 2 days.  (04-19-14  04-21-14)
